SIFAX Group has clocked 31 years. It is not a mean feat that the company has not only survived a very harsh business environment over the years, but has also experienced a phenomenal growth, with expansion into various sectors of the country’s economy as well as on the international stage. The outlook for the future is even brighter. L-R: Kelly Imade, Senior Manager, Administration; Abiodun Elemide, Group Compliance Coordinator; Barr. Ezekiel Ajewole, Executive Director and Senior Special Assistant to Barr. (Dr.) Taiwo Afolabi, Group Executive Vice Chairman; Olushola Adebote, Assistant General Manager, Audit and Oluwakayode Alonge, Group Head, Human Resources all of SIFAX Group during the 31st Anniversary celebration of the company which was held at its Head Office located at Apapa.  Barrister Ezekiel Ajewole, Executive Director and Senior Special Assistant to Barr. (Dr.) Taiwo Afolabi, Group Executive Vice Chairman, SIFAX Group with other managers and Heads of Department during the 31st Anniversary celebration of SIFAX Group which was held at its Head Office located at Apapa.  Barrister Ezekiel Ajewole, Executive Director and Senior Special Assistant to Barr. (Dr.) Taiwo Afolabi, Group Executive Vice Chairman, SIFAX Group with female staff during the 31st anniversary celebration of SIFAX Group which was held at its Head Office located at Apapa.  Staff during SIFAX Group’s 31st anniversary celebration which was held at its Head Office, Apapa recently.